      @pytest.mark.asyncio
      async def test_backup_verification(self, test_export_dir):
          """Test backup data verification."""
          # Create backup with checksum
          backup_data = {
              "timestamp": datetime.now().isoformat(),
              "sources": [],
              "articles": [],
              "checksum": "mock_checksum"
          }

          backup_file = test_export_dir / "verified_backup.json"
          with open(backup_file, 'w') as f:
              json.dump(backup_data, f)

          # Verify backup
          with open(backup_file) as f:
              data = json.load(f)
              assert "checksum" in data
              assert data["timestamp"] is not None

  ‚Ä¢ api             API endpoint tests (~2m)
  ‚Ä¢ integration     System integration tests (~3m)
  ‚Ä¢ ui              Web interface tests (~5m)
  ‚Ä¢ e2e             End-to-end tests (~3m)
  ‚Ä¢ performance     Performance tests (~2m)
  ‚Ä¢ ai              AI Assistant tests (~3m)
  ‚Ä¢ ai-ui           AI UI tests only (~1m)
  ‚Ä¢ ai-integration  AI integration tests (~2m)
  ‚Ä¢ all             Complete test suite (~8m)
  ‚Ä¢ coverage        Tests with coverage report

üí° Usage Examples:
  $ python run_tests.py smoke
  $ python run_tests.py all --coverage
  $ python run_tests.py --docker integration
  $ python run_tests.py --debug --verbose
  $ python run_tests.py unit --fail-fast
